# Brief — STOW-RS upload endpoint

## Context

Users need to upload DICOM studies via STOW-RS. The API contract is locked
in `docs/contracts/api-todo.md` (merged to main). Work stays inside the
`backend-dev` lane; frontend consumption is issue 43.

## Acceptance criteria

- POST /studies accepts multipart DICOM per the contract
- Rejects non-DICOM payloads with 415
- Stores accepted instances and returns the contract's success shape

## Testable Check

pytest tests/test_stow.py — all cases pass, including the 415 rejection case.
